Codes describing the physical accessibility to buildings and parts of buildings.

No obstacles, easy to get an overview.
Codes defining how information is provided.
Audio signals, wire loop, noise in the area, announcements, etc.
Clarity with respect to naming and directions, font size, etc.
Placing, lightening, contrast end reflection, fonts used, visibility from waiting area, etc.
Address how information services are provided.

Contrast colours on furniture, doors and frames, making of glass doors and glass walls, etc

Codes describing problem areas related to allergy.

Codes defining available utilities and facilities.

<font color="#19161b">A railway transport usually consisting of two parallel rails on which a powered- vehicle or train machine pulls a connected series of vehicles to move them along the railway in order to transport freight or passengers from one destination to another. </font>
<font color="#19161b">Train-like transport vehicle limited to a rail network within a limited area. </font>

<font color="#19161b">A railway transport system used in urban areas, which often runs at street level, sharing road space with motor traffic and pedestrians. Tramways are usually electrically powered. </font>

<font color="#19161b">A railway transport which allows the vehicles to operate on steep gradients, consisting of a railway provided with a toothed rack rail (usually between the running rails) where vehicles are fitted with one or more cog wheels or pinions that mesh with this rack rail. </font>
<font color="#19161b">A railway transport based on a single rail which acts as both its only support and guideway. </font>
<font color="#19161b">A railway transport based on a single rail, acting as both support </font>

<font color="#19161b">A railway transport consisting of a cable attached to a vehicle on rails which moves them up and down a very steep slope. Where possible the ascending and descending vehicles counterbalance each other. </font>
<font color="#19161b">A railway transport based on a single rail which acts as guideway of a vehicle and supports it by means of a magnetic levitation mechanism. </font>

<font color="#19161b">An urban railway transport system used in large urban areas, which runs on a separate track from other transport systems, is usually electrically powered and in some cases runs under ground </font>
<font color="#19161a">A cableway transport whose vehicles consist of a suspended cabin for carrying groups of people and/or goods inside it from one location to another. </font>

<font color="#19161a">A cableway transport whose vehicles consist of suspended chairs for carrying individuals or groups of people from one location to another via a steel cable or rope which is looped around two points. </font>
<font color="#19161a">A cableway transport for pulling skiers and snowboarders uphill</font>
